now for reading and doing research in Computer Science Theory.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-09T18:25:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mostafatouny/awesome-theoretical-computer-science","categoryHTML":"<h2>TCS Inspired</h2><h3>Lecture Notes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.cmu.edu/~odonnell/toolkit13/\">O'Donnell. A Theorist's Toolkit</a> - It covers a large number of the math/CS topics that you need to know for reading and doing research in Computer Science Theory.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-09T18:25:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mostafatouny/awesome-theoretical-computer-science","categoryHTML":"<h2>TCS Inspired</h2><h3>Lecture Notes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.princeton.edu/courses/archive/fall07/cos597D/Site/lectopics.html\">Arora. Thinking Like a Theorist</a> - It covers a large number of the math/CS topics that you need to know for reading and doing research in Computer Science Theory.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-09T18:25:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mostafatouny/awesome-theoretical-computer-science","categoryHTML":"<h2>TCS Inspired</h2><h3>Lecture Notes</h3>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.princeton.edu/courses/archive/fall02/cs597D/\">Arora. A Theorist's Toolkit</a> - Aimed primarily at first and second year graduate students who plan to do research in theoretical computer science. We will introduce probabilistic, algebraic, combinatorial, and algorithmic methods useful in proofs.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-09T18:25:27.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mostafatouny/awesome-theoretical-computer-science","categoryHTML":"<h2>Lecture Notes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.princeton.edu/courses/archive/fall15/cos521/\">Arora. Advanced Algorithm Design</a> - Notably uses ideas such as randomness, approximation, high dimensional geometry. Faces uncertainty, approaches to handle big data, handling intractability, heuristic approaches, ..etc.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-09T18:21:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mostafatouny/awesome-theoretical-computer-science","categoryHTML":"<h2>Lecture Notes</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.cs.princeton.edu/courses/archive/spring11/cos116/lectures.php\">Arora. The Computational Universe</a> - Takes us on a broad sweep of scientific knowledge and related technologies: propositional logic of the ancient Greeks (microprocessors); quantum mechanics (silicon chips); network and system phenomena (internet and search engines); computational intractability (secure encryption); and efficient algorithms (genomic sequencing).</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-09T18:21:48.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"Fr0sT-Brutal/awesome-pascal","categoryHTML":"<h2>Logging</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/jachguate/jachLogMgr\">jachLog</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/jachguate/jachLogMgr\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">28</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":28,\"repo\":\"jachguate/jachLogMgr\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END-->. <code>[Delphi]</code> pure pascal, flexible, extensible and lightweight library to add logging capabilities to your Delphi applications. Multiple log destinations supported. The library supports multithreaded applications and is itself multithreaded to minimize the impact writing the log may have on the performance on mission critical applications.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-03-09T18:00:56.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"mostafatouny/awesome-theoretical-computer-science","categoryHTML":"<h2>Discrete Mathematics</h2><h3>Books</h3>","